review_text:
Decent content, but non-essential. 

Shieldbreaker class is fun to play with, serving as a sort of glass-cannon with a few interesting blight/armor ignoring attacks to deal with high protection enemies, along with her Serpent's Sway, a limited use ability that prevents all damage from the next two attacks. However, it should be clarified that the new monsters come up in an ambush that can only occur when you use her; they're not encountered beyond that scope, and it's kind of annoying. Imagine, if you will, the Collector mini-boss could only show up whenever you camped with the Flagellant. It's an interesting battle, but kind of gamey and arbitrary in its application, and that's how it feels here to me. Hopefully a mod turns it into a general encounter like has been done with the Shrieker, but until then;

Decent content, but non-essential.
